  "correctAnswer": "0.3,3/10",
  "section": "Math",
  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Substitute x equals 6",
      "content": "Replace $x$ with 6 in the function $f(x) = \\frac{x-3}{x^2-7x+16}$:<br><br>$$f(6) = \\frac{6-3}{6^2-7(6)+16}$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Evaluate the numerator and denominator",
      "content": "<strong>Numerator:</strong> $6 - 3 = 3$<br><strong>Denominator:</strong> $36 - 42 + 16 = 10$<br><br>$$f(6) = \\frac{3}{10} = 0.3$$"
    }
  ]
}